Two people drowned at Maitlands Beach on Tuesday afternoon. Emergency rescue services responded to reports of a drowning in progress shortly after 1pm and found the bodies of two people in the water. NSRI Port Elizabeth confirmed  their team was dispatched to Maitlands Beach at about 1.30pm and assisted in recovering the  bodies. The names of the  two have not been released  and the circumstances surrounding  the incident are still unknown. HeraldLIVE